19:19.852 --> 19:21.789
That's why it has to be her.

19:23.860 --> 19:26.899
‐ Apple pie and plain oatmeal.

19:26.899 --> 19:29.605
Extra, extra, extra milk.
No flies.

19:29.605 --> 19:31.341
Enjoy.

19:31.943 --> 19:33.513
‐ He's a damn psychopath.

19:33.513 --> 19:34.582
‐ I just farted!

19:34.582 --> 19:36.619
‐ Max said, "I just‐‐"
‐ I heard that.

19:36.619 --> 19:38.255
I heard that part.

19:38.255 --> 19:40.827
‐ Oh, now the kids are leaving.
Oh, wait.

19:40.827 --> 19:42.798
Asta just came in.

19:42.798 --> 19:44.334
‐ Like musical chairs in here.

19:46.271 --> 19:49.277
‐ You are late.
I finished eating without you.

19:49.277 --> 19:51.214
‐ I think you'll survive.

19:51.214 --> 19:54.220
‐ I prefer to eat with you.
You order a lot of food.

19:54.220 --> 19:57.260
I like to forage
off of your plate.

19:57.260 --> 20:00.499
‐ Well, maybe you should
try foraging off

20:00.499 --> 20:03.540
someone else's plate, hm?

20:03.540 --> 20:05.977
I'm like your only friend.

20:05.977 --> 20:07.981
‐ I need only one friend.

20:07.981 --> 20:11.589
And one bunker butler,
but I'm working on that.

20:11.589 --> 20:14.294
Maybe that one.

20:14.294 --> 20:16.833
No, she looks like
she may leave hair

20:16.833 --> 20:18.937
on the wall of the shower.

20:20.372 --> 20:21.843
‐ I think you should spend
more time

20:21.843 --> 20:23.580
with some other people in town.

20:25.249 --> 20:27.386
‐ I have met
all the other people in town.

20:27.386 --> 20:29.692
They are annoying
flesh monkeys.

20:29.692 --> 20:31.929
‐ Okay, come on.
You got it.

20:31.929 --> 20:34.568
Here we go.

20:34.568 --> 20:36.371
Hey, Liv.
‐ Hi.

20:36.371 --> 20:39.010
‐ Sheriff, Harry would like
to join your weekly poker game.

20:39.010 --> 20:41.549
‐ Oh, really?
Huh.

20:44.354 --> 20:48.429
‐ Asta said I do, so I do.

20:48.429 --> 20:49.765
‐ Oh, you know what,
Dr. Vanderspeigle?

20:49.765 --> 20:51.334
That'd be real nice.

20:51.334 --> 20:52.470
It'd give us a chance
to get to know one another.

20:52.470 --> 20:54.542
‐ Okay.
You going to finish that?

20:57.013 --> 20:59.384
‐ No, go right ahead.
‐ Thank you.

21:00.854 --> 21:02.490
‐ You see that?

21:02.490 --> 21:04.027
Now, I don't know no normal man
that eat that much pie.

21:04.027 --> 21:05.496
I don't care how good it is.

21:05.496 --> 21:08.402
‐ This, too, eh?
I mean, thank you.

21:11.308 --> 21:13.479
[electronic music]

21:13.479 --> 21:15.750
‐ Okay, players.
Game is Texas hold 'em.

21:15.750 --> 21:19.357
Tournament style, $20 buy‐in.
Quarter for the small blind.

21:19.357 --> 21:21.662
50¢ for the big blind.
There are only three rules.

21:21.662 --> 21:24.869
No spitting, no crying,
and no funny business.

21:24.869 --> 21:25.937
This guy knows
what I'm talking about.

21:25.937 --> 21:27.039
‐ [fake laughs]

21:27.039 --> 21:28.442
‐ I am glad I am here.

21:28.442 --> 21:29.812
This game will
give me a chance

21:29.812 --> 21:33.018
to audition more potential
helpers for our bunker.

21:33.018 --> 21:36.024
Is anybody here worth saving?

21:36.024 --> 21:38.696
‐ All right, well, let's get
this show on the road.

21:38.696 --> 21:40.065
‐ ♪ This is a raid ♪

21:40.065 --> 21:42.671
‐ Oh, and everybody
welcome Harry who says

21:42.671 --> 21:45.075
he knows how to play.

21:45.075 --> 21:46.646
I call bullshit,
but he's a rich doctor,

21:46.646 --> 21:48.048
so I'm gonna take him
for all he's worth

21:48.048 --> 21:50.085
and buy a new pair
of roller skates.

21:50.085 --> 21:51.789
‐ I know how to play.

21:51.789 --> 21:54.929
I spent 15 minutes on YouTube
to master this silly game,

21:54.929 --> 21:58.870
and I mostly just watched
videos of a dog named Tuna.

21:58.870 --> 22:01.408
‐ Oh, careful there.

22:01.408 --> 22:04.982
This card table is actually
a Hawthorne family heirloom.

22:04.982 --> 22:06.117
‐ Wish there was a story
about the table.

22:06.117 --> 22:07.621
‐ Are you shitting me...
‐ John.

22:07.621 --> 22:08.823
‐ Right now?
‐ Oh, there is actually.

22:08.823 --> 22:10.426
It once belonged

22:10.426 --> 22:12.631
to my two‐times great
grandfather Dickie Hawthorne.

22:12.631 --> 22:13.633
He built‐‐
‐ Why?

22:13.633 --> 22:15.402
‐ The first saloon here
in Patience.

22:15.402 --> 22:17.373
Burned down
in the great fire of '91,

22:17.373 --> 22:19.077
but old Dickie,
he risked his life

22:19.077 --> 22:22.618
to save this very table
that we're playing on tonight.

22:22.618 --> 22:24.487
‐ Didn't three people die
in that fire?

22:24.487 --> 22:25.389
‐ Four.

22:25.389 --> 22:26.859
‐ The thing to focus on,
I think,

22:26.859 --> 22:28.428
is that the table is here.

22:28.428 --> 22:30.432
It should actually be
in the town museum,

22:30.432 --> 22:32.370
but someone
keeps on taking it out.

22:32.370 --> 22:34.742
‐ We should probably just kiss
and make up.

22:34.742 --> 22:36.679
‐ She's kidding.
We're‐‐I'm very‐‐

22:36.679 --> 22:38.415
‐ We kiss a lot though,
so it's weird.

22:38.415 --> 22:40.419
‐ In high school,
we dated briefly.

22:40.419 --> 22:41.589
‐ Yeah, and recently,
we made out.

22:41.589 --> 22:42.991
‐ [chokes]

22:42.991 --> 22:44.595
She's kidding.

22:44.595 --> 22:48.035
‐ ♪ This is a raid
so put your hands up ♪

22:48.035 --> 22:51.141
♪ We're gonna win this ♪

22:51.141 --> 22:54.648
♪ Take the mon‐mon‐money,
this is a raid ♪

22:54.648 --> 22:55.884
‐ What about this one?

22:55.884 --> 22:58.556
Maybe he has use
to me in the bunker?

22:58.556 --> 23:02.096
‐ Can you cook?
‐ Sure, I cook every night.

23:02.096 --> 23:03.967
‐ Pie?
‐ Vegetables.

23:03.967 --> 23:05.837
Raw, if I can,
for the nutrients.

23:05.837 --> 23:08.543
‐ I‐‐
‐ Like to eat healthy stuff.

23:08.543 --> 23:09.912
‐ Pass.

23:09.912 --> 23:13.519
I would rather just fill
the bunker with bales of hay.

23:13.519 --> 23:17.026
Time to separate the boys
from the men from the girls.

23:17.026 --> 23:18.630
‐ ♪ This is a raid ♪

23:18.630 --> 23:21.903
‐ Risk taker, interesting.

23:21.903 --> 23:25.476
‐ I'll raise.
Better be careful.

23:25.476 --> 23:27.881
Don't want you
to go broke again.

23:27.881 --> 23:30.820
‐ Broke?
What you talking about?

23:30.820 --> 23:34.895
‐ Rumor has it our doctor lost
all his money six years ago.

23:34.895 --> 23:37.868
Tried to sell his cabin
to my uncle.

23:37.868 --> 23:39.638
‐ I did not sell my cabin.

23:39.638 --> 23:41.709
‐ Yeah,
you backed out of the deal,

23:41.709 --> 23:44.147
which is why I'll enjoy
taking all your money tonight.

23:44.147 --> 23:45.684
No one can figure out

23:45.684 --> 23:48.690
how you managed
to hang on to that place.

23:48.690 --> 23:50.794
‐ You getting all this?
‐ I'm getting it.

23:50.794 --> 23:51.896
‐ Anybody got some gum?

23:51.896 --> 23:53.065
‐ No, no, no, no, no.

23:53.065 --> 23:54.868
‐ I can sure
use a piece of gum.

23:54.868 --> 23:56.505
I had an onion sandwich.

23:56.505 --> 23:57.908
It's in everybody's
best interest.

23:57.908 --> 23:59.678
‐ Don't mind me.

23:59.678 --> 24:02.784
I'm just gonna rake
in this pile of chips here.

24:02.784 --> 24:06.091
The good news is when I do win,
all of this money

24:06.091 --> 24:09.565
