26:51.087 --> 26:53.024
You got the most important job
in the world.

26:53.024 --> 26:54.393
You a stay‐at‐home mom

26:54.393 --> 26:56.364
to our three kids
Alvin, Simon, and Theodore.

26:56.364 --> 26:57.901
Actually, you know what?
Scratch that.

26:57.901 --> 26:59.237
Now, I wasn't
gonna say nothing,

26:59.237 --> 27:00.740
but you looking
a little tired.

27:00.740 --> 27:02.978
Probably got like five kids.

27:02.978 --> 27:05.683
Ooh, this is nice.

27:05.683 --> 27:08.956
‐ Well, hello there.
I am Bonnie Shaw.

27:08.956 --> 27:10.760
I'm showing the house today.
‐ Hi.

27:10.760 --> 27:12.998
‐ Justine Preacher.
How do you do?

27:12.998 --> 27:15.670
I'm a big‐time
sports broadcaster.

27:15.670 --> 27:18.208
This is my cute,
little husband Mr. Preacher.

27:18.208 --> 27:20.245
He stays at home
with our five kids.

27:20.245 --> 27:22.717
And that's why
he looks so tired.

27:22.717 --> 27:27.928
‐ Wow, let's take a look
at the kitchen first, Mr. Mom.

27:27.928 --> 27:30.432
