‐ Yeah, well, I'm also
a licensed helicopter pilot,

27:32.838 --> 27:35.008
and I put out fires
with swimming pool water.

27:35.008 --> 27:38.048
‐ Well, you must be busy.

27:40.085 --> 27:42.156
‐ This is nice,

27:42.156 --> 27:46.164
but we were looking for
something a little more rustic.

27:46.164 --> 27:49.170
Do you know anything about that
red cabin off of Cove Road,

27:49.170 --> 27:50.840
over in Patience?

27:50.840 --> 27:53.178
It's got a private beach.
We saw it online.

27:53.178 --> 27:55.917
‐ It's funny you should ask.
That's the Vanderspeigle cabin.

27:55.917 --> 27:57.888
I listed that myself
a couple years ago,

27:57.888 --> 27:59.892
and it's off
the market right now,

27:59.892 --> 28:03.398
but sometimes,
owners can be convinced.

28:03.398 --> 28:06.104
You know, honestly,
the doc who owns it,

28:06.104 --> 28:07.373
he might be a little bit
of work.

28:07.373 --> 28:08.943
He's a real mystery.

28:08.943 --> 28:09.978
‐ So you know him?

28:09.978 --> 28:11.314
‐ Oh, honey,

28:11.314 --> 28:14.855
knowing everything about
my clients is my business.

28:14.855 --> 28:16.024
‐ I like that.

28:16.024 --> 28:21.267
♪ ♪

28:23.338 --> 28:24.841
‐ Hey.
‐ Hey.

28:24.841 --> 28:26.444
‐ How's it going?

28:26.444 --> 28:28.448
‐ It's all right.
I'm just waiting for my mom.

28:28.448 --> 28:32.223
She's shopping for towels.

28:32.223 --> 28:36.264
‐ Oh, cool, so what's new?

28:36.264 --> 28:38.970
‐ I got my driver's license.
‐ Whoa.

28:38.970 --> 28:41.341
‐ I can't really parallel park
for shit, but...

28:41.341 --> 28:42.811
‐ Me neither.
‐ Jay.

28:42.811 --> 28:46.384
Honey, why don't you
go start the car?

28:46.384 --> 28:49.123
You can drive us home.
‐ Cool.

28:49.123 --> 28:50.960
Later.
‐ Later.

28:53.098 --> 28:56.906
‐ I always wondered if I would
ever meet Jay's birth mother.

28:56.906 --> 29:01.749
I wanted to someday,
but reuniting a child

29:01.749 --> 29:04.487
with her birth parent
is up to the child.

29:04.487 --> 29:07.126
You know that, right?

29:07.126 --> 29:09.531
‐ Um...

29:09.531 --> 29:11.936
I'm sorry.
What I did was wrong.

29:11.936 --> 29:16.912
It's just there she was,
you know, like, at the clinic

29:16.912 --> 29:22.256
asking for work‐study,
and, well, I crossed a line.

29:22.256 --> 29:23.993
I just really wanted
to help her.

29:23.993 --> 29:26.799
‐ I will never stop Jay from
wanting to be in your life,

29:26.799 --> 29:30.907
but she has to be the one
to cross the street, not you.

29:30.907 --> 29:32.777
♪ ♪

29:32.777 --> 29:36.217
‐ I know.

29:36.217 --> 29:37.386
‐ Okay.

29:37.386 --> 29:44.534
♪ ♪

29:46.004 --> 29:47.373
‐ So six years ago,
he puts his cabin on the market

29:47.373 --> 29:48.876
'cause he needs the money.

29:48.876 --> 29:50.112
‐ Mm‐hmm.

29:50.112 --> 29:52.016
‐ Only to turn around and
pay the whole damn thing off

29:52.016 --> 29:53.485
in cash one week later?

29:53.485 --> 29:55.355
‐ Half a million in cash.

29:55.355 --> 29:58.328
‐ That's some shady shit
right there.

29:58.328 --> 30:01.034
‐ Do you think he's
a contract killer?

30:01.034 --> 30:02.469
‐ Now, that's a good guess.

30:02.469 --> 30:03.873
Man, ain't no honest man

30:03.873 --> 30:05.008
got that much liquid
just laying around.

30:05.008 --> 30:06.545
Hell, I only got 90K
in the bank,

30:06.545 --> 30:08.315
and that's just
for emergencies.

30:08.315 --> 30:10.285
‐ 90,000?

30:10.285 --> 30:14.026
That's‐‐seems like a lot.

30:14.026 --> 30:15.162
‐ Eh.

30:15.162 --> 30:17.166
[engine grinding]

30:17.166 --> 30:18.836
‐ Is there a problem, Deputy?

30:18.836 --> 30:21.307
‐ Oh, it just needs
a new starter.

30:21.307 --> 30:23.178
My mechanic can
do it for parts,

30:23.178 --> 30:27.854
but I don't have the $65.

30:27.854 --> 30:30.258
‐ Oh.

30:30.258 --> 30:33.933
Well, you know, I was probably
rounding up to that 90 anyway.

30:33.933 --> 30:36.839
It's probably somewhere like,
I don't know, 85, 87.

30:36.839 --> 30:38.909
Just enough for a rainy day.

30:38.909 --> 30:40.278
‐ Mm‐hmm.

30:40.278 --> 30:44.086
‐ Okay, I'ma get out and push.

30:53.606 --> 30:55.042
[soft music] ‐ I think it's cool

30:55.042 --> 30:57.212
you're gonna make
a commercial for Patience.

30:57.212 --> 31:00.018
‐ Yeah, maybe if I show
some pretty pictures

31:00.018 --> 31:02.256
of our town, people
will want to come visit.

31:02.256 --> 31:04.326
‐ They already do.
‐ Hm?

31:04.326 --> 31:06.230
‐ My friend Scott said
all his California cousins

31:06.230 --> 31:08.168
want to come here this summer
to see dead bodies.

31:08.168 --> 31:10.506
‐ What?
‐ Wait, or a murder.

31:10.506 --> 31:12.476
Hey, maybe I can play
a dead guy in your commercial.

31:12.476 --> 31:14.313
‐ No, no dead guys.

31:14.313 --> 31:18.321
Max, Patience is a beautiful
and safe‐‐very safe town.

31:18.321 --> 31:20.993
There are no dead bodies here.

31:20.993 --> 31:23.899
‐ And this is where
our town doctor

31:23.899 --> 31:26.270
was brutally murdered
by his wife.

31:26.270 --> 31:29.544
The doctor who replaced him
went missing,

31:29.544 --> 31:32.316
but we expect his body
to turn up any day now.

31:32.316 --> 31:34.487
Oh, don't forget to enter
the corpse raffle.

31:34.487 --> 31:38.428
‐ What the hell is this?
‐ Look, everyone.

31:38.428 --> 31:41.267
It's our town mayor,
Ben Hawthorne.

31:41.267 --> 31:44.240
Great‐great‐grandson
of Dickie Hawthorne

31:44.240 --> 31:47.379
who died the day
the mine collapsed,

31:47.379 --> 31:50.318
but not with his fellow miners.

31:50.318 --> 31:53.391
No, Dickie called in sick
that day.

31:53.391 --> 31:55.663
His wife found him
in the whorehouse

31:55.663 --> 31:58.268
and shot him in the face.

31:58.268 --> 32:00.973
‐ I'm related to him.
‐ No, just an old rumor, buddy.

32:00.973 --> 32:02.677
Old rumor, not true.

32:02.677 --> 32:05.182
‐ We're walking.
Come on.

32:05.182 --> 32:07.152
Take your pictures
if you'd like.

32:07.152 --> 32:08.622
♪ ♪

32:10.425 --> 32:12.296
‐ Come on.
Let's get a move on, Deputy.

32:12.296 --> 32:15.469
‐ Sir, you're not gonna believe
who just returned my call.

32:15.469 --> 32:19.276
St. Helens Hospital said Dr.
Vanderspeigle was disciplined

32:19.276 --> 32:22.216
after they found him in a lab
he wasn't authorized to be in.

32:22.216 --> 32:23.686
And do you know
what they kept stored there?

32:23.686 --> 32:25.222
‐ What?
‐ Botulinum toxin.

32:25.222 --> 32:27.660
‐ Are you shitting me?
Damn.

32:27.660 --> 32:30.600
We might have put
the wrong person behind bars.

32:30.600 --> 32:32.704
‐ Looks like it's time
to talk to Dr. Vanderspeigle.

32:32.704 --> 32:34.273
‐ Yeah.

32:34.273 --> 32:35.610
‐ But first, I have to drop off
this dry cleaning.

32:35.610 --> 32:37.045
‐ What?

32:37.045 --> 32:38.582
Justice doesn't wait
for no dry cleaning.

32:38.582 --> 32:40.553
‐ It's half‐price Tuesdays.

32:40.553 --> 32:42.089
‐ This is some shit here.

32:42.089 --> 32:43.726
‐ People, stay together.
We have a lot to see.

32:43.726 --> 32:45.195
‐ Oh, my God.

32:45.195 --> 32:48.301
‐ Oh, another
special treat today.

32:48.301 --> 32:51.307
Here we have
the Patience sheriff

32:51.307 --> 32:57.186
who single‐handedly put
the wife of Sam Hodges in jail.

32:57.186 --> 33:00.258
Rumor has it she's close
to death in her prison cell,

33:00.258 --> 33:05.168
rats waiting to feast
on her killer corpse.

33:05.168 --> 33:07.740
We're walking.
Bye, handsome.

33:07.740 --> 33:13.519
♪ ♪

33:13.519 --> 33:15.455
[cell phone chimes]

33:15.455 --> 33:19.631
♪ ♪

33:19.631 --> 33:21.802
[radio scanning]

33:21.802 --> 33:23.572
‐ You're listening to 102.6,

33:23.572 --> 33:25.342
and we have a special listener
request on the line.

33:25.342 --> 33:27.379
What do you want us to play?

33:27.379 --> 33:29.618
‐ Hey, I'd like you to play
The Breeders' "Off You"

33:29.618 --> 33:31.487
for my best friend Asta,

33:31.487 --> 33:33.592
and tell her, if she needs me,
I'll always come running.

33:33.592 --> 33:38.301
‐ Wait, I know this voice.
D'arcy?

33:38.301 --> 33:39.403
‐ [in Russian accent]
D'arcy?

33:39.403 --> 33:42.309
No, this Sasha.
Hello, yes.

33:42.309 --> 33:44.714
‐ Yeah, D'arcy.
We dated for five months.

33:44.714 --> 33:47.554
I think I know your voice,
and the night we broke up

33:47.554 --> 33:49.524
you stole six bottles
of wine out of my fridge.

33:49.524 --> 33:51.795
‐ I don't have
no stealing wine.

33:51.795 --> 33:54.701
Only vodka, so okay.
Play song for best friend.

33:54.701 --> 33:56.170
‐ Jesus.
‐ And then go.

33:56.170 --> 33:58.642
‐ Fine.
Here's The Breeders I guess.

33:58.642 --> 34:01.648
[soft guitar music]

34:01.648 --> 34:08.762
♪ ♪

34:09.330 --> 34:14.708
‐ ♪ I land to sail,
island sail ♪

34:14.708 --> 34:18.414
♪ ♪

34:18.414 --> 34:20.720
♪ Yeah, we're movin' ♪

34:20.720 --> 34:23.391
♪ ♪

34:23.391 --> 34:26.798
♪ Yeah, we're movin' ♪

34:26.798 --> 34:34.113
♪ ♪

34:38.589 --> 34:40.559
‐ Harry?

34:40.559 --> 34:45.836
♪ ♪

34:45.836 --> 34:48.474
Hello?

34:48.474 --> 34:50.746
What's the big surprise?

34:50.746 --> 34:53.786
♪ ♪

34:53.786 --> 34:57.125
[metal clanking]

35:04.306 --> 35:06.110
Harry?

35:06.110 --> 35:09.116
[tense music]

35:09.116 --> 35:12.590
♪ ♪

35:12.590 --> 35:14.561
Harry?

35:14.561 --> 35:16.497
♪ ♪

35:16.497 --> 35:19.436
Harry?

35:19.436 --> 35:26.417
♪ ♪

35:29.624 --> 35:31.360
What the hell is this?

35:31.360 --> 35:36.738
‐ My survival shelter
and your new home.

35:36.738 --> 35:38.709
[soft music]

35:38.709 --> 35:40.746
You can choose the rugs.

35:40.746 --> 35:42.215
♪ ♪

35:48.796 --> 35:50.332
‐ Why do you have
a fallout shelterunder your house?

35:50.332 --> 35:55.308
‐ I built it for us,
so that we can be safe

35:55.308 --> 35:58.381
when my people come
to kill everyone.

35:58.381 --> 35:59.851
‐ What?

35:59.851 --> 36:01.922
‐ Oh, I forgot to tell you.

36:01.922 --> 36:04.694
My people are coming
to kill everyone.

36:04.694 --> 36:06.330
‐ When?

36:06.330 --> 36:10.171
‐ Octopus thinks it may be
a matter of weeks.

36:10.171 --> 36:11.608
Whoops.

36:11.608 --> 36:13.512
‐ Hello again, stupid human.

36:13.512 --> 36:15.549
‐ God, I hate when you do that.

36:15.549 --> 36:18.789
‐ The bathroom
will be over here

36:18.789 --> 36:23.632
if they come before
I get a real toilet,

36:23.632 --> 36:25.803
we can use this bucket.

36:25.803 --> 36:27.940
It is unisex.

36:27.940 --> 36:32.583
Oh, and I am getting a cow
if I can figure out

36:32.583 --> 36:34.821
how to get it
through the opening.

36:34.821 --> 36:37.693
‐ You're joking, right?
‐ You are right.

36:37.693 --> 36:39.798
The opening is too small.

36:40.800 --> 36:42.970
I may get a baby cow
and raise it.

36:42.970 --> 36:45.976
‐ Harry, this is not okay.

36:45.976 --> 36:47.714
This was all supposed
to be over with.

36:47.714 --> 36:49.551
Why are your people coming?

36:49.551 --> 36:53.424
‐ They are‐‐how did you put it?

36:53.424 --> 36:58.267
‐ Oh, it was "eager
to fry all you Earth pigs."

36:58.267 --> 36:59.938
‐ That.

36:59.938 --> 37:02.442
‐ I can't do this.
No, no, no.

37:02.442 --> 37:05.716
You expect me to live
underground with you for weeks?

37:05.716 --> 37:09.389
‐ Oh, no.
It will be at least a year.

37:09.389 --> 37:13.397
I know that you like
the out‐of‐doors.

37:13.397 --> 37:15.335
I painted you a window.

37:15.335 --> 37:18.675
You can enjoy
the beautiful Colorado scenery.

37:18.675 --> 37:22.482
♪ ♪

37:22.482 --> 37:25.623
Feel the breeze.

37:25.623 --> 37:27.727
Those are dead people.

37:27.727 --> 37:29.931
That is the stupid boy.

37:29.931 --> 37:35.475
You cannot see his frown
because my brush was too thick.

37:35.475 --> 37:37.713
‐ Nope, this isn't happening.
I'm not doing it.

37:37.713 --> 37:39.551
I'm not living in a hole
in the ground with you

37:39.551 --> 37:41.320
and that octo‐thing.

37:41.320 --> 37:42.289
‐ Oh, wait.

37:42.289 --> 37:43.491
‐ Well, that's fine with me.

37:43.491 --> 37:44.761
You think I want
to spend the next year

37:44.761 --> 37:46.363
watching you shit in a bucket?

37:46.363 --> 37:47.667
‐ Shh‐shh!

37:47.667 --> 37:50.004
‐ Huh.

37:50.004 --> 37:52.810
‐ Don't go.
It will be fun.

37:52.810 --> 37:56.350
Octopus knows
so many cuttlefish jokes.

37:56.350 --> 37:57.720
They are so stuck up.

37:57.720 --> 37:59.691
‐ You're not
taking me seriously.

37:59.691 --> 38:01.561
‐ Pizza.

38:02.362 --> 38:04.901
‐ You have to do something
about this,

38:04.901 --> 38:08.040
and hiding us underground
for a year isn't it.

38:08.040 --> 38:10.713
You're an alien.
You know, phone home.

38:10.713 --> 38:13.384
Call them,
and tell them not to come.

38:13.384 --> 38:16.725
‐ Did I tell you that we are
going to have all 20 seasons

38:16.725 --> 38:18.729
of "Law & Order" to watch?

38:18.729 --> 38:20.599
‐ Oh, God.

38:20.599 --> 38:24.039
I would rather die than be
on this planet with just you.

38:24.039 --> 38:26.978
‐ Rude.
‐ You don't get it.

38:26.978 --> 38:29.517
So what, I'm just supposed to
come out after the apocalypse,

38:29.517 --> 38:30.920
and everyone I know is dead?

38:30.920 --> 38:33.725
I'm here all alone?

38:33.725 --> 38:35.629
‐ Also rude.

38:35.629 --> 38:40.438
‐ I'm talking about my family.
What about Dad and D'arcy?

38:40.438 --> 38:41.942
What about Jay?

38:41.942 --> 38:44.413
God, no.
Don't you understand?

38:44.413 --> 38:46.918
I can't live here if I have
to live without all of them.

38:46.918 --> 38:48.856
So there you go, call them,

38:48.856 --> 38:51.427
and tell them not to come,
or I will just die.

38:51.427 --> 38:54.701
‐ I know what this is.

38:54.701 --> 38:58.341
You are bluffing,
like in poker.

38:58.341 --> 39:00.411
♪ ♪

39:00.411 --> 39:02.617
‐ No, I'm not!

39:02.617 --> 39:04.888
I would rather stand under
your stupid planet's death ray

39:04.888 --> 39:06.457
and explode
into a million pieces

39:06.457 --> 39:09.564
than spend one second
in that hole with you.

39:09.564 --> 39:11.000
‐ She is good at bluffing.

39:11.000 --> 39:13.104
I could possibly contact them,

39:13.104 --> 39:15.943
but I want to kill
all the bags of douches.

39:15.943 --> 39:18.381
It is my turn to bluff.

39:18.381 --> 39:19.951
♪ ♪

39:19.951 --> 39:23.725
It's impossible.
I cannot contact them.

39:23.725 --> 39:25.428
‐ Now you're bluffing.

39:25.428 --> 39:26.898
‐ I am bad at bluffing.

39:26.898 --> 39:31.541
‐ Okay, okay.
I'll call your bluff.

39:31.541 --> 39:33.979
♪ ♪

39:33.979 --> 39:37.452
If you don't mind
that I die, good.

39:37.452 --> 39:41.393
‐ What are you doing?
‐ I think I'll take a bath.

39:41.393 --> 39:44.032
♪ ♪

39:44.032 --> 39:48.742
‐ You are not really going
to electrocute yourself.

39:48.742 --> 39:52.850
♪ ♪

39:52.850 --> 39:56.423
‐ I've got the toaster
all plugged in.

39:56.423 --> 39:58.895
Whoo, nice and warm.
Really good way to go out.

39:58.895 --> 40:00.498
Call it off, Harry.

40:00.498 --> 40:02.904
‐ I told you I cannot.

40:02.904 --> 40:06.645
I do not like this game.
The stakes are too high.

40:06.645 --> 40:09.584
You are not really
in the bathtub.

40:09.584 --> 40:10.853
If the toaster is plugged in,

40:10.853 --> 40:12.623
it is because
you are making toast.

40:12.623 --> 40:13.892
Asta.

40:13.892 --> 40:15.729
♪ ♪

40:15.729 --> 40:18.167
You didn't bring the bread.

40:18.167 --> 40:21.641
♪ ♪

40:21.641 --> 40:23.879
This is very dangerous.

40:23.879 --> 40:26.483
‐ Then agree
to call your people.

40:26.483 --> 40:28.689
‐ Okay.

40:28.689 --> 40:34.934
♪ ♪

40:34.934 --> 40:37.540
It went straight to voicemail.

40:37.540 --> 40:39.476
♪ ♪

40:39.476 --> 40:41.615
‐ Goodbye, Harry.

40:41.615 --> 40:47.760
♪ ♪

40:47.760 --> 40:48.962
See?

40:48.962 --> 40:50.766
I knew you didn't
want me to die.

40:50.766 --> 40:52.469
You just took your damn time
showing it.

40:52.469 --> 40:55.108
‐ Of course I do not
want you to die.

40:56.076 --> 40:59.550
I will try to build a radio
to contact my people.

41:01.153 --> 41:03.925
Be careful getting
out of the tub.

41:03.925 --> 41:05.696
Don't slip.

41:05.696 --> 41:08.134
‐ Coming from you, that's
a very sweet thing to say.

41:10.038 --> 41:12.777
‐ I'm going
to go eat pizza now.

41:20.659 --> 41:23.164
♪ ♪

41:23.164 --> 41:25.903
[knocking]

41:25.903 --> 41:27.740
‐ I'm just gonna keep knocking.

41:27.740 --> 41:29.711
I got hands
that can knock all day.

41:29.711 --> 41:31.514
[knocking]

41:31.514 --> 41:33.117
Dr. V., open up.

41:33.117 --> 41:35.522
We know you're in there.
We need to speak with you.

41:35.522 --> 41:37.593
Don't make us come back
with a search warrant.

41:37.593 --> 41:40.532
♪ ♪

41:40.532 --> 41:42.102
Hello, Asta, need to speak

41:42.102 --> 41:44.106
with Dr. Vanderspeigle
about that severed foot.

41:44.106 --> 41:45.576
‐ He's not here.

41:45.576 --> 41:47.546
‐ Look, don't lie to me.

41:47.546 --> 41:50.586
We saw him eating pizza through
the window when we rolled up.

41:50.586 --> 41:52.122
‐ I'm not lying.

41:52.122 --> 41:54.192
‐ Asta, I'm telling you
this as a friend.

41:54.192 --> 41:55.896
Harry is not
who you think he is.

41:55.896 --> 41:58.267
He could be dangerous.
Please don't protect him.

41:58.267 --> 42:00.873
‐ Uh...

42:00.873 --> 42:03.010
Maybe come back later?

42:03.010 --> 42:04.747
‐ Look, if I have to arrest you

42:04.747 --> 42:06.283
for obstruction
of justice, I will.

42:06.283 --> 42:09.657
Talking about some
"come back later."

42:09.657 --> 42:12.963
Shit!
What the hell is this?

42:12.963 --> 42:14.767
Hold on.

42:14.767 --> 42:21.815
♪ ♪

42:24.921 --> 42:28.027
Oh, my goodness.
Well, I'll be.

42:28.027 --> 42:32.035
Deputy, what's that say
right there?

42:32.035 --> 42:34.607
Botulinum toxin.
The murder weapon.

42:34.607 --> 42:36.143
‐ Oh, no.

42:36.143 --> 42:38.247
‐ All right, look,
I'ma ask you one more time.

42:38.247 --> 42:41.921
Where is he, Asta?
Where is he, Asta?

42:41.921 --> 42:44.025
♪ ♪

42:44.025 --> 42:46.196
‐ He went
to hide in the cellar.

42:46.196 --> 42:48.200
♪ ♪

42:48.200 --> 42:50.171
‐ You wait here.

42:50.171 --> 42:52.977
Dr. V.?

42:52.977 --> 42:55.248
Sheriff's department.
We coming down into the cellar.

42:55.248 --> 42:56.918
